5000|$|A ready <b>berth</b> <b>clause</b> is {{inserted}} in a charter-party, i.e. a stipulation {{to the effect}} that laydays will begin to count as soon as the vessel has arrived at the port of loading or discharge [...] "whether in berth or not". It protects shipowner's interests against delays which arise from ships having to wait for a berth.|$|E

